Due to recent changes in Confluence, the OnDemand Confluence Importer is currently unable to import from versions of Confluence >= 5.2.

One example of this can be seen in the {{PersonalInformationPreprocessor}} which attempts to cache {{PersonalInformation}} objects for use in the {{UserPostImportTask}} (to later associate {{UserDetails}} with users). The preprocessor incorrectly assumes {{PersonalInformation}} objects contain {{username}} fields (which, as of 5.2 they now contain {{user}} fields with associated user keys).

As this is just one example of the plugin making incorrect assumptions this ticket is intended to address all of these issues (by revisiting all pre/postprocessors)

