When creating some parent/child pages using the Page Properties Macro, and the Page Properties Report Macro we are wanting to set the properties across where the Field Name is on the top, and the value is below it (i.e. two rows, multiple columns).

The Page Properties Report Macro works just with the data in this format.  However, the formatting that is visible on the while editing the page with the Page Properties Macro is not carried over when the page is displayed.  In other words, if I go to the "child" page with the Page Properties in it, I have the top row bolded with a color background.  But once I save the page, the left column is shown in bold and with a color background.  If I move the table outside of the macro field, the style/color settings are displayed correctly.  It's only when it's inside the Page Properties Macro.  And, again, the Page Properties Report macro on the "parent" page displays the data just fine.

